# Project Workflow

- After editing code or docs, automatically verify formatting and validity before reporting completion.
- For TypeScript, JavaScript, JSON, and Markdown changes, run `pnpm run format` when formatting may be affected, then run `pnpm run check` for subscription validation.
- Do not run `pnpm run build` only for a local git commit; GitHub Actions generates the `dist` subscription files.
- Do not stage or commit generated `dist/*` changes from local formatting, checking, or merge resolution unless the user explicitly asks for built output.
- If a command changes files, review the resulting diff and stage only source, config, or documentation changes that are part of the requested work.
- Do not claim the work is complete until the relevant verification command has passed, or clearly state which verification could not be run.
